descript.abstract:
This dataset incorporates datasets containing major canal features from varying agencies, including the California Department of Water Resources, the United States Bureau of Reclamation, LA Department of Water & Power, and East Bay Municipal Utility District. Conflicts between these data sources and spatial inaccuracies were resolved using **** imagery from 2006???. Any digitizing was done at approximately a 1:9000 scale.Many unnamed canals were identified using USGS topo maps and the ESRI Street Map layer. These layers were also used as the basis to modify or add canal features.
The dataset represents an improved consolidated dataset for canal features over previous versions. This dataset attempted to pull various available datasets together into one location, clear up any overlaps and conflicting names, and improve the accuracy. But due to the fact that it is a "best available" type effort and full research on canals throughout the State was not warranted by the Program improving the data, additional major canal features may exist, errors in attribution may be present, and further improvements in spatial accuracy may be possible.
descript.purpose: General inventory and mapping of major canal features of California. Primarily suited for regional or statewide mapping. Should not be used for precise engineering or survey purposes.
